flowRoot.flowPara: Anaconda splash is the first screen of Anaconda graphical interface. It takes place after Anaconda prompt and hardware detection.
Anaconda splash visual style is based on CentOS default artistic motif and controlled by Anaconda header (image-a) and Anaconda splash image (image-b).

Both Anaconda header and splash images include the CentOS Symbol, the CentOS release brand, and the CentOS Logotype. Both Anaconda header and splash images are visually connected by CentOS Default Artistic Motif..

flowRoot.flowPara: The CentOS Symbol: Inside anaconda header (image-a), the CentOS symbol. Inside anaconda splash (image-b), the CentOS symbol is 64 pixels height.

The CentOS Release Brand: Inside anaconda header (image-a), the CentOS release brand is 48 pixels height. Inside anaconda splash (image-b), the CentOS release brand is 64 pixels height without descritption, and around 94 pixels height with description. Note that CentOS release brands, both in header and splash images, are built using the CentOS LogoType plus the major release number (e.g., 5 in this case).
